      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im stuck at heathrow cuz my flight to singapore just got canceled... everything is a mess here. can u help me figure out what i should look for in new flights? i need to get there as fast as possible so what should i prioritize when looking at options?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm so sorry to hear your flight got canceled; that is an incredibly stressful situation, and I hope the airport staff can help you get rebooked quickly. Since you need to get to Singapore as fast as possible, you should prioritize flights with the shortest total travel time, including connection times, rather than just the flight duration itself. Look for direct flights if available, as they eliminate the risk of missing a connecting flight, which is a major headache when things are already chaotic. You might also want to check if the airline has rebooked you on a different flight automatically, as sometimes they handle this better than third-party sites.\n\nWhile you are searching for options, keep your eyes open for any \"giant\" notices or announcements in the terminal, as they often have the most up-to-date information on rebooking procedures. If you are feeling overwhelmed, remember that the airport staff are there to help you navigate this mess, and you can ask them to alert you if a new flight becomes available. Just stay calm, keep your documents handy, and don't forget to check your phone for any SMS updates, as those can sometimes be faster than the screens.\n\nI wish you a smooth transition to your next flight, and I hope",
